hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Polariton dispersion relation:  
   $$k^2 c^2 \;=\;\omega^2\,\varepsilon(\omega)\,.$$

2. Thus  
   $$k \;=\;\frac{\omega}{c}\sqrt{\varepsilon(\omega)}\,,$$  
   and the momentum is  
   $$p \;=\;\hbar k \;=\;\frac{\hbar\,\omega}{c}\sqrt{\varepsilon(\omega)}\,.$$

3. Dielectric function for one TO mode:  
   $$\varepsilon(\omega)
     =\varepsilon_{\infty}\,\frac{\omega_{LO}^2-\omega^2}{\omega_{TO}^2-\omega^2}\,.$$

4. Lyddane–Sachs–Teller relation:
   $$\frac{\omega_{LO}^2}{\omega_{TO}^2}=\frac{\varepsilon_{s}}{\varepsilon_{\infty}}
   \quad\Longrightarrow\quad
   \omega_{LO}^2=\omega_{TO}^2\frac{\varepsilon_{s}}{\varepsilon_{\infty}}\,.$$

5. Evaluate at $\omega=\omega_{TO}/2$:
   $$\omega^2=\frac{\omega_{TO}^2}{4},$$
   $$\omega_{LO}^2-\omega^2
     =\omega_{TO}^2\frac{\varepsilon_{s}}{\varepsilon_{\infty}}
      -\frac{\omega_{TO}^2}{4}
     =\omega_{TO}^2\Bigl(\frac{\varepsilon_{s}}{\varepsilon_{\infty}}-\frac14\Bigr),$$
   $$\omega_{TO}^2-\omega^2
     =\omega_{TO}^2-\frac{\omega_{TO}^2}{4}
     =\frac{3\omega_{TO}^2}{4}\,.$$

6. Hence
   $$\varepsilon\bigl(\tfrac{\omega_{TO}}{2}\bigr)
     =\varepsilon_{\infty}
      \frac{\omega_{TO}^2\bigl(\frac{\varepsilon_{s}}{\varepsilon_{\infty}}-\frac14\bigr)}
           {\frac{3\omega_{TO}^2}{4}}
     =\varepsilon_{\infty}\frac{4}{3}\Bigl(\frac{\varepsilon_{s}}{\varepsilon_{\infty}}-\frac14\Bigr)
     =\frac{4\varepsilon_{s}-\varepsilon_{\infty}}{3}\,.$$

7. Finally,
   $$p
     =\frac{\hbar\,\omega}{c}\sqrt{\varepsilon(\omega)}
     =\frac{\hbar\,(\omega_{TO}/2)}{c}
      \sqrt{\frac{4\varepsilon_{s}-\varepsilon_{\infty}}{3}}
     =\frac{\hbar\,\omega_{TO}}{2c}
      \sqrt{\frac{4\varepsilon_{s}-\varepsilon_{\infty}}{3}}\,.$$
